these bank facilities allow for borrowings at libor-based rates plus a spread, which
depends on the companys public debt rating and can range from 0.175% to 0.75%. as of october3, 2009, the company had not borrowed under these bank facilities. the company also has the ability to issue up to $800 million of letters of
credit under the facility expiring in 2011, which if utilized, reduces available borrowing under this facility. as of october3, 2009, $326 million of letters of credit had been issued of which $237 million was issued under this facility.
