$4.5 billion. during fiscal 2007, the company repurchased 202million shares of disney common stock for $6.9 billion. on may1, 2007, the board of directors of the company increased the share repurchase authorization to a total of
400million shares. as of october3, 2009, the company had remaining authorization in place to repurchase 179million additional shares. the repurchase program does not have an expiration date.  in april 2008, the company redeemed $1.3 billion of convertible senior notes. pursuant to the redemption, substantially all of the notes
